class WeatherSimulator {
    private int temperature;
    private boolean isRaining;

    public WeatherSimulator(int temperature) {
        this.temperature = temperature;
        this.isRaining = false;
    }

    public void updateWeather(int deltaTemp, boolean startRain) {
        temperature += deltaTemp;
        if (startRain && temperature < 20) {
            isRaining = true;
        } else {
            isRaining = false;
        }
    }

    public boolean willItRain() {
        return isRaining && temperature < 15;
    }
}",

If the temperature is initially set to 25 degrees and later the temperature drops due to deltaTemp without any intervention to start rain, can it start raining?
